    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We conducted weekly surveillance for SARS-CoV-2 infection among a sample of households with \u22651 child aged 0-17 years from selected Utah counties. A Cox proportional hazards model approach was used to calculate infection hazard rate and vaccine effectiveness. Findings show that the recommended primary series of COVID-19 vaccine was effective against circulating variants during a Delta-predominant wave in Utah.</jats:p>",
